        <article>
            <h1>Understanding CSS Concepts</h1>
            <p><strong>Box Model in CSS:</strong> The box model in CSS defines the design and layout of elements on a webpage. It consists of content, padding, border, and margin. The <em>box-sizing</em> property is used to define how the total width and height of an element are calculated. It can have two values: <mark>content-box</mark> (default) or <mark>border-box</mark>.</p>
            <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRrbgSyY-segOeh1fbdZLaAgLUXS8NEiipUWrjAJj4ucg&s" alt="Box Model">

            <h2>CSS Hacks:</h2>
            <p><strong>Clearfix Hack:</strong> The clearfix hack is a technique used to clear floated elements within a container. It is applied when the container's height collapses due to floating elements inside it.</p>

            <h3>Margin Collapse and Usage:</h3>
            <p><strong>Margin Collapse:</strong> Margin collapse occurs when the vertical margins of two adjacent elements are combined into a single margin. The <mark>margin: auto</mark> property is used to center an element horizontally within its parent, while negative margin values can be used for overlapping elements or creating unique layouts.</p>
            <img src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:421/0*kAD00byJs8jdmXvr.png" alt="Margin Collapse" width=200>
            <img src="https://csswolf.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/margin-shorthand-declared-with-2-values.svg" alt="Margin Values" width=200>

            <h4>The Holy Grail Layout:</h4>
            <p>The Holy Grail layout refers to a web design pattern with a header, footer, and three columns of content. The problem with achieving this layout traditionally was the complexity of equal-height columns.</p>

            <h4>Modern Solutions:</h4>
            <p>Modern ways to achieve the Holy Grail layout include using flexbox or CSS grid layouts. These provide more flexible and responsive options for creating complex layouts without the need for hacks.</p>
            <img src="https://www.computerhope.com/issues/pictures/gridhg_00-diagram.jpg" alt="Holy Grail Layout" width=200>
        </article>
